Relay Development Fixed Prompts and Commands

Chinese natural-language triggers you can say directly:
- `接手这个项目，按接力开发规则来`
- `给这个项目初始化接力开发`
- `重新同步当前任务`
- `做一次标准交接`
- `按接力开发流程处理这个项目`

1) Session Start
Touch context in this order, using summary-first reading by default:
`AGENTS.md -> task_registry.md -> progress.md -> task_plan.md -> findings.md -> 修改记录_会话备忘.md`
Default reading granularity:
- `AGENTS.md`: read fully.
- `task_registry.md`: read only the active `Task-ID` row first.
- `progress.md`: read `Latest Handoff Snapshot` first.
- `task_plan.md`: read the current task section, latest plan, open TODO, and risks first.
- `findings.md`: read recent facts related to the same `Task-ID` first.
- `修改记录_会话备忘.md`: read the most recent 1-3 relevant `Session Record` entries first.
Only expand to full-file reading if the user explicitly asks, the context conflicts, or the current task cannot be reconstructed from summaries.
Pick or create a Task-ID first and declare Task-Name.
Then output a "Session Context" summary with:
- Task-ID / Task-Name
- Developer/Branch(or No-Git)
- Active Goal
- Current Phase
- Next First Command
- Open TODO Top3
Run startup checks and continue from `Current Phase`.

2) Before Handoff Stop
Update `progress.md` -> `Latest Handoff Snapshot` with:
`Task-ID, Task-Name, Files Changed, Completed This Session, Open TODO, Risks/Blockers, Next First Command`
Append one Session Record entry in `修改记录_会话备忘.md`.
Update the same Task-ID row in `task_registry.md` (Status, Last Update, Next First Command).
Output a one-line handoff summary and stop.

3) Cross-App Resume
After switching tools, re-read startup context order with summary-first reading, lock to the same Task-ID, restate Task-ID / Active Goal / Current Phase / Next First Command, then execute Next First Command.

4) In-App Model Switch Resume
After switching model in the same app, re-read startup context order with summary-first reading, lock to the same Task-ID, restate Task-ID / Active Goal / Current Phase / Next First Command, continue remaining work only.

5) Blocked State Report
If any required read/check/command fails, stop execution and output:
Status: BLOCKED
Failed Step:
Reason:
Missing File / Failed Command:
Suggested Fix:
Next First Command (Fallback):

6) Same Tool + Same Model + Different Session Resume
I switched to another session in the same tool and same model for `Task-ID=XXX`.
Re-read startup context with summary-first reading, keep only this Task-ID context, mark other tasks as `IGNORE`, then continue with this Task-ID only.

